object: A logical data type which judges whether given statement is TRUE or FALSE
functions: 
  Boolean And(a,b)      ::= if (a==b==TRUE) return TRUE
                            else return FALSE
  Boolean Or(a,b)       ::= if (a==b==FALSE) return FALSE
                            else return TRUE
  Boolean Not(a)        ::= if (a==TRUE) return FALSE
                            else return TRUE
  Boolean Xor(a,b)      ::= if (a==b) return FALSE
                            else return TRUE
